content:
This component handles the user sign-up process for the DocMed application. It integrates with Clerk for authentication and provides a visually engaging sign-up form with email verification.

## Features

*   **Email/Password Sign Up**: Users can sign up using their email address and a chosen password.
*   **Email Verification**: After initial sign-up, users are prompted to enter a verification code sent to their email.
*   **Google OAuth Sign Up**: Offers a "Continue with Google" option for a faster sign-up experience.
*   **Animated UI**: Employs animated components (`AnimatedForm`, `Ripple`, `TechOrbitDisplay`, `BoxReveal`) for a modern and engaging user interface.
*   **Error Handling**: Displays user-friendly error messages during the sign-up and verification process.
*   **Responsive Design**: Adapts to different screen sizes, with a dedicated orbit display on larger screens.

## Key Components and Hooks

*   **`useSignUp` (from `@clerk/nextjs/legacy`)**: Hook to manage the sign-up flow, including creating users, preparing email verification, and attempting verification.
*   **`useRouter` (from `next/navigation`)**: Used for programmatic navigation after successful sign-up or verification.
*   **`AnimatedForm`**: A custom component likely encapsulating the form input fields and submit button with animations.
*   **`Ripple`**: A component that creates a ripple effect, likely used for background visual appeal.
*   **`TechOrbitDisplay`**: Displays icons in an orbital pattern, serving as a prominent visual element on the left side of the page.
*   **`BoxReveal`**: Animates the appearance of content within a "box".
*   **`Input` and `Label`**: Custom UI components for form elements.

## State Management

*   `email`: Stores the user's email address.
*   `password`: Stores the user's password.
*   `code`: Stores the verification code entered by the user.
*   `pendingVerification`: A boolean flag indicating whether the user is in the email verification stage.
*   `error`: Stores any error messages encountered during the process.
*   `loading`: A boolean flag to indicate if an asynchronous operation (sign-up, verification) is in progress.

## Usage Example (Conceptual)

The component renders based on the `pendingVerification` state. If `false`, it displays the initial sign-up form. If `true`, it shows the email verification form.

```tsx
// In app/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx

// ... imports and OrbitIcon component ...

export default function SignUpPage() {
  // ... state and hook initializations ...

  // handleSubmit function for initial sign-up
  const handleSubmit = async (_event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) => {
    // ... sign-up logic using signUp.create and signUp.prepareEmailAddressVerification ...
    setPendingVerification(true);
  };

  // handleVerify function for email code verification
  const handleVerify = async (e: FormEvent) => {
    // ... verification logic using signUp.attemptEmailAddressVerification ...
    if (result.status === "complete") {
      await setActive({ session: result.createdSessionId });
      router.push("/dashboard");
    }
  };

  // handleGoogleSignUp function for OAuth
  const handleGoogleSignUp = async () => {
    await signUp.authenticateWithRedirect({
      strategy: "oauth_google",
      redirectUrl: "/sso-callback",
      redirectUrlComplete: "/dashboard",
    });
  };

  return (
    <section className="flex min-h-screen bg-background">
      {/* Left — orbit display */}
      <span className="hidden lg:flex ...">
        {/* ... TechOrbitDisplay and Ripple components ... */}
      </span>

      {/* Right — form */}
      <span className="w-full lg:w-1/2 ...">
        <div className="w-full max-w-md">
          {!pendingVerification ? (
            <>
              <AnimatedForm
                // ... formFields props ...
                onSubmit={handleSubmit}
                onGoogleLogin={handleGoogleSignUp}
                // ... other props ...
              />
              <p>
                Already have an account?{' '}
                <Link href="/sign-in">
                  Sign in
                </Link>
              </p>
            </>
          ) : (
            /* Email verification step */
            <section className="flex flex-col gap-5 w-96 mx-auto">
              {/* ... verification form elements ... */}
              <form onSubmit={handleVerify}>
                <Input
                  // ... code input props ...
                  value={code}
                  onChange={(e) => setCode(e.target.value)}
                />
                <button type="submit">{loading ? "Verifying..." : "Verify email"}</button>
              </form>
              <button type="button" onClick={() => setPendingVerification(false)}>
                ← Back to sign up
              </button>
            </section>
          )}
        </div>
      </span>
    </section>
  );
}
